reviews_data.review_text: We would’ve loved to support this spot, but our visit was a complete disappointment. When we walked in, the employee was slumped in a chair behind the counter, completely asleep, and never woke up the entire time we were there. No greeting, no service—nothing. Needless to say, we left and took our business elsewhere.

I’ve been to some Middle Eastern coffee spots, but Coffee Origin really stands out. The quality of the coffee here is smooth and rich. The guy who runs it is seriously the nicest. He remembered us even though it had been a couple of weeks, which made the whole experience feel even more welcoming.

The atmosphere is super calm and perfect if you’re trying to study, journal, or just enjoy a good drink. It’s rare to find a coffee shop that’s both this cozy and this quiet. Definitely one of my new favorite spots.
They are super friendly! I love the adeni chai and the bee bites are so amazing! My friend got the pistachio latte and was also very good

The Turkish coffee is a must! The coffee variety is impressive but even more so is the actual authenticity ! So impressed that I made multiple visits during my few day trip. The staff is also fantastic very welcoming and knowledgeable. I would highly recommend skipping starbucks and dunkin get your coffee here if you have the chance it’s well worth the visit.
I usually get a salted caramel latte and it’s so good. The staff is really nice! I love this place and I don’t usually give reviews
They have variety of chai and coffee offerings, including those from Yemen. The staff are friendly and there is a lot of seating space.
Great place! I've gotten the mango refresher twice and the chocolate croissant, it was delicious!

Unassuming exterior, but inside awaits a friendly staff and sweet coffee treats. The staff offered my friend’s daughter a treat for free and was very helpful in recommending drinks for us. I had an iced Spanish Latte upon the staff’s recommendation and it was very tasty and reasonably priced; definitely recommend if you like your coffee on the sweeter side! The sitting area was clean, open, spacious, and quiet.
Came here after another coffee shop was closed today, and was pleasantly surprised at this spot. Great, strong, HOT coffee and really tasty pastries and cheesecakes.
Solid coffee and iced drinks with Yemeni choices beyond the usual coffee house menu. Good pastries and plenty of room inside.
Delicious latte, grateful it's open so late because I needed a coffee before a long drive home
Best chai ever.

I can’t believe I’ve waited this long to stop in this coffee shop. I pass it all the time and I have been missing out. I guess I was under the impression that you had to go through the smoke shop to go to the coffee shop and I was wrong. It has its own entrance. The coffee was so good, I would say it’s the best I’ve had in a while. My favorite is the Dulce de leche latte. My daughter loved the Ube latte. I have only one suggestion. Music!! It’s a little too quiet and some music would make the whole place come together. Great space for working and meeting up with people. They are open late for those that can’t ever find a coffee shop open past 5pm unless it’s a chain shop.
Uber eats, order the pistachio milk cake with a Spanish latte and added hazelnut. It was delightful!! Will order again yumm

Very friendly staff and eclectic cafe offering coffee, tea, and pastries with an Arabic influence. I had the Spanish latte and it was perfectly balanced. Our barrister Abd (nickname Joe) is an artist.

What a nice surprise — in Mount Holly. My first time to enjoy cardamom coffee! The pastry is delicious — but pricey. Nice atmosphere. I am enjoying the Arabic music. When there are finishing touches on the construction and decor, I will confidently give a 5 star rating.

Feb 3, 2025
I revisited Origins this morning and enjoyed a freshly brewed cup of delicious cardamom coffee and a very tasty chocolate croissant.

The finishing touches on the dining area are lovely. It’s like having a mini vacation to a far land while enjoying the artwork and the music.

After reading the other comments, I think I may have to try a pistachio latte next time😁!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
**Dear [Nora Rollins],**

Thank you for visiting us and for sharing your experience! We’re so glad you enjoyed the cardamom coffee and found our atmosphere to your liking, especially with the Arabic music. We’re also happy to hear that the pastry hit the spot, even if it felt a bit on the pricey side—your feedback is invaluable as we continue refining our offerings.

We appreciate your patience as we put the finishing touches on the space and look forward to providing you with an even better experience next time. Hope to see you again soon!

Warm regards,  
[Moe]  
[Manager]  
[Origin Coffee]

reviews_data.review_text: What a delightful experience.  My husband and I stopped by thirty minutes before closing and we're so glad we did.  The staff member on duty was kind and courteous despite the late hour.  I had the chocolate croissant and red tea.  The croissant was so flaky, warm and delicious.  The red tea was a delicious, flavorful tea with wonderful hints of cardamom.  My husband had the pistachio latte which was excellent!  The staff member was attentive and the establishment was clean.  I highly recommend Coffee Origin and I can't wait to visit again.

Finally visited this coffee shop and it was very good. The coffee was high quality  and the 2 baked treats were good/fresh. They have a really cool purple couch to sit on. I will definitely be back to try some different things. My only complaint would be for families, it’s connected to a smoke shop and they might not like that. Although some might actually like that feature. Give this place a try!
Great coffee and service!

The best coffee I've had in a very long time! I came in to do some paperwork on my computer sat down and before I knew it I had this lovely presentation for my coffee which was outstanding, I was extremely pleasantly surprised when I took my first sip. It was very pretty but I was not expecting the flavor to be so spot on. I honestly can't remember the last time  I have  had coffee this good and I love coffee. The girl who made it was incredibly polite and kind. The service was excellent. It was a quiet atmosphere. I will definitely be back. I have a huge comfortable couch where you can sit at a table, but it's a big open space and it doesn't feel cramped or overcrowded. This is my second time there. I also did have the coffee cake milk cake which was again out of this world. I asked that they had tiramisu and she recommended the coffee cake because they did not and I was not disappointed at all. I found a new dessert that I absolutely love. I did notice that the girl who works there skipped over the part where I'm allowed to tip her on the computer system I had to ask her for her copy of the receipt so I could write down her tip on there & it. She was just going to give me my receipt and nowhere to tip.  and she did the same thing when my mom went to pay her as well because my mom came and met me and I didn't know what coffee she wanted two separate transactions. So if you go and you get this wonderful young lady I recommend tipping her and maybe doing it in cash to make sure that she is able to get her to because I don't think she gets paid enough.  I know when Mount Holly finds out about this gem it'll get crowded and not be a quiet place to work anymore but I'll still go back for the coffee! I cannot express enough that I can't remember the last time that I have had coffee that tasted this good!
The coffee and the pastries are delicious. The exceptional customer service of the friendly staff added to the great experience. This is a must visit place in Mount Holly.

Every time we go, the owner Yusuf is so nice. His coffees and baked goods are wonderful. Now that it’s getting colder we’ll have to drop by to try his hot drinks. We’ve loved his caramel frappes, match frappes with almond milk, cinnamon rolls, and another baked good called Sabaya with flaky baklava crust but topped with honey and sesame seeds. The shop is always clean and comfortable, we love visiting.
Great service and Amazing drinks.

Absolutely phenomenal! The atmosphere was warm and inviting and the service was amazing. They have Something for everyone as well. If you like Middle Eastern coffee or want to try it they have a lot to pick from and they also have regular lattes, macchiatos, etc. If you’re a fall drink lover like I am I highly recommend the pumpkin pie latte! Easily the best fall drink I’ve had. I will definitely be going back!

Just opened and worth your visit.

They can shorten the other items on t menu to one type of cake & cheesecake slices and/or sweet potato pie. Simple.👍. To keep the focus on coffees

I got a Mufuaar- which was very good! I loved the cardamom.
I can’t wait to go back and try some other drinks!

Also they often come out very hot - careful!

I highly recommend you give this new, unique coffee shop a try. I know I will certainly be back!
